Amazing Cruise in a Breathtaking Location
Aug 2017 ‚Ä¢ Family
We were welcomed aboard the Junk ship by the friendly, helpful and attentive crew and served with a welcome lunch of Vietnamese delicacies all prepared and beautifully presented by their young aspiring Chef. We were then taken to a cave in which there were stalagmites and stalagtites. Towels, footware and polyethelene rain macks were provided. We were then taken kayaking then back to the Junk Ship for an evening of yet more culinary delights, a short film of the cruise, fishing and star gazing.
