Sally R
Leeds, UK51 contributions
4.0 of 5 bubbles
Similar visually to Tam Coc and Bai Tu Long
Stayed overnight on a boat but a day tour would be more than enough as the overnight boats only offer 12 hours on the water, 7 of which you are asleep!

Bai Tu long bay is part of the same area just with a different name and no overnight boats. Head there for a quieter more authentic sail. You won't be missing out on not visiting ha long bay because it is just another name for the same area!
Thoroughly recommend visiting Trang An near Ninh Binh to see karst from a more intimate characterful setting.
Written May 16, 2017
Roger J
Wellington, New Zealand12 contributions
Great Scenery but avoid GOLDEN BAY CRUISE!!
Apr 2017 ‚Ä¢ Friends
Ha long bay it self was beautiful. Great scenery and enjoyed the tour to Surprise cave, and beach, although over crowded. We mistakenly booked through another operator, rather than the one we were recommended (FANTASEA Tours) and chose to do a one night tour.
Our accommodation was good, complete with ensuite with hot water, and good pressure.
Lunch was good on the first day, whole fish, pickled vege, rice, tofu and cabbage. This unfortunately was my favourite meal. 500ml bottles of water were US$1 a bottle (24VND) which was normally 7VND, we were told nothing that was purchased from the ship could be consumed on the ship. If drinks or alcohol was bought on to the ship a duty would have to be paid.
In the afternoon we were taken to the Surprise caves. The ques were long , as there were many other tour companies arriving at the same time, this also occurred at the beach we visited.
The bar onboard, commence with happy hour over the duration of the tour, buy 2 get 1 free. The drinks were still cheapish (US$2/50VND but not in comparison to Hanoi town (10/15VND) wine was priced at US$30 and was TERRIBLE.
As part of the cost of the tour, we were told of a 20l keg was supplied for the paying customers. There was a clause, the "Free beer" was only for an hour. I found out from the tour guide, after an hour the beer was given to the crew. With that; I grabbed and empty 1.5l water bottle and filled this up before the hour was up, and shared this around once the keg was taken off us. ( apparently it was almost empty when they took it, and they werent happy)
Our tour guide tried to induce us to drink more by stating 'happy hour' was back on, and said you guys dont know how to "party". With that people were saying to him the drinks were expensive, why we had to pay US$1 for water etc. In the end, I think he was got annoyed about it and headed below deck.
our breakfast, was a rubbery fried egg, partially toasted bread, fried rice cake, and coffee. We were then told to "get off the boat" for a compulsory tour of a pearl farm. At the completion of the tour, we returned we conducted a "cooking class" , this was more like rolling up summer rolls for lunch, not actually cooking.
To sum it all up, the views were great the crowds werent, and this Company; Ha Long Golden bay cruise was the WORST!!
Top Tips;
Smuggle your own water and alcohol, keep it in your room.
Drink as much 'free beer' as you can, collect it in a large bottle (dont get caught)
Read reviews about other tour companies first.
I hope this helps.
Written April 28, 2017
Jewel236
Melbourne, Australia346 contributions
Overnight cruises will cease in 2020
Mar 2017 ‚Ä¢ Friends
There is so much competition on HaLong Bay for the tourist dollar, for both day trips & overnight cruises. Make sure you do some research beforehand to enable the best experience & value.
The Vietnamese government has declared that overnight cruises will not be permitted after 2020 (partly environmental but also driven by huge hotel development to ensure economic viability).
If this is on your bucket list, better get cracking!
Written March 24, 2017
jsthouston
Houston, TX6,192 contributions
Worth the trip
Feb 2017 ‚Ä¢ Couples
While it is three hours from Hanoi to the bay by car, and four if you're on a shared shuttle it is worth the trip if you spend a night on a cruise, or in a local hotel and do a day cruise. We did a two night cruise and I would say that the decision to spend that much time on the water depends on the weather at the time.
